OL,3,CIs Europe too hot for school holidays?
OL,4,CChoosing a destination by its weather
OL,6,FWe're regularly seeing temperatures
OL,7,Fsoar close to and exceeding 40C by
OL,8,Fday and barely dropping below 30C
OL,9,Fovernight in many European locations.
OL,11,FThe sea does help regulate
OL,12,Ftemperatures but it doesn't make
OL,13,Fplaces immune to heat.
OL,15,FCoastal areas usually have smaller
OL,16,Ftemperature swings, because the ocean
OL,17,Fheats and cools more slowly than land.
OL,19,FThe source of the heat also matters.
