OL,3,CIs Europe too hot for school holidays?
OL,4,CChoosing a destination by its weather
OL,6,FIn France, northern Spain and Portugal
OL,7,Fis influenced by a cooler sea, but
OL,8,Fduring persistent high-pressure
OL,9,Fpatterns, clear skies and light winds
OL,10,Ftemperatures will climb. The normal
OL,11,Fcooling influence can weaken.
OL,13,FIslands can trap heat. Islands have
OL,14,Fless land area, but they can still
OL,15,Fheat up significantly under strong
OL,16,Fsunshine, especially where there is
OL,17,Fdry ground, little cloud and shelter
OL,18,Ffrom the wind. They may not reach the
OL,19,Fextremes of inland areas, but
OL,20,Fprolonged heat can still be
OL,21,Funcomfortable.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
