OL,3,CIs Europe too hot for school holidays?
OL,4,CChoosing a destination by its weather
OL,6,FWarm nights are the hidden issue. The
OL,7,Fsea can actually keep overnight
OL,8,Ftemperatures higher because it
OL,9,Freleases stored heat slowly.
OL,11,FThe Mediterranean Sea has consistently
OL,12,Fbroken records with increased water
OL,13,Ftemperatures year on year - it's known
OL,14,Fas 'the bath tub affect'.
OL,16,FAs this body of water is mostly
OL,17,Fsurrounded by land and is relatively
OL,18,Fshallow, it retains heat more than
OL,19,Fopen ocean.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
